verses.roman:
eta bali' mahāprabhu uṭhiyā calilā
govinda-dvārāya duṅhe prasāda pāṭhāilā

synonyms: eta bali'-saying this; mahāprabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; uṭhiyā calilā—got up and left; govinda-dvārāya—through Govinda; duṅhe—to both of them; prasāda pāṭhāilā—sent prasāda.
translation: Having said this, Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu got up and left, and through Govinda He sent prasāda for them to eat.
